<exercise checkit-seed="0008" checkit-slug="LimitCont" checkit-title="Continuity">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>Determine the value of <m>b</m> to make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=-1</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        f(x) = \begin{cases}
                        b x + 5 \, x^{2} - 6, &amp; x \leq -1 \\\
                        \frac{1}{2} \, x + \frac{7}{2}, &amp; x &gt; -1
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>The function <m>g(x)</m> is discontinuous at <m>x=-2</m>. Determine if <m>g(x)</m> is left- or right-continuous and classify the type of discontinuity present at <m>x=-2</m>.</p>
                <p>
                    <me>
                        g(x) = \begin{cases}
                        -x, &amp; x \leq -2 \\\
                        \frac{x^{2} + 10 \, x + 24}{x^{2} + 5 \, x + 6}, &amp; x &gt; -2
                        \end{cases}
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>To make <m>f(x)</m> continuous at <m>x=-1</m>, let <m>b=-4</m>.</li>
            <li>The function <m>g(x)</m> has a infinite discontinuity and is left-continuous at <m>x=-2</m>.</li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
